        content: "An emergency fund is the foundation of financial security. Without one, every unexpected expense becomes a debt emergency. Financial experts recommend 3-6 months of essential expenses (not income — expenses). If your monthly needs are $2,000, aim for $6,000-12,000. But start with $1,000 as your first milestone. Keep it in a high-yield savings account (HYSA) — accessible but separate from your checking so you're not tempted. Automate $25-50/week and you'll hit $1,000 in 5-10 months. What counts as an emergency? Car repair, medical bill, job loss, essential appliance breaking. What's NOT an emergency? Sales, vacations, new shoes, concerts.",
        takeaway: "Start with $1,000, then build to 3-6 months of expenses. Keep it in a separate high-yield savings account.",
        quote: { text: "It wasn't raining when Noah built the ark.", author: "Howard Ruff" },
